Executive Profile
Andrew L. Farkas  Founder, Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and Managing Member, Island Capital Group LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships57--
Background

		Mr. Andrew L. Farkas, also known as Andy, serves as the Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of C-III Capital Partners LLC. Mr. Farkas is a Non-Managing Partner at BayStar Capital, Baystar Capital III, L.P. and Baystar Capital II, L.P. He is a Strategic Partner at Charterhouse Group, Inc. (now Charterhouse Equity Partners LLC). Mr. Farkas founded Island Capital Group LLC in May 2003 and serves as its Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and Managing Member. Mr. ... Farkas also serves as an officer in various subsidiaries and controlled affiliates of Island Capital Group LLC. He serves as an Advisor at i-Hatch Ventures LLC. He served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Island Global Yachting Ltd. He founded Insignia Financial Group, Inc. in 1990 and served as its Chairman from May 1998 to 2003 and Chief Executive Officer and President from January 1991 to 2003. Prior to Insignia Financial Group, Inc., Mr. Farkas was employed at Thompson McKinnon Securities from 1982 to 1984. He served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Insignia Properties Trust since January 1997. Mr. Farkas was the Founder and Managing Principal of Metropolitan Asset Group, Ltd. since 1984. He founded Island Global Yachting Ltd. in 2005 and serves as its Chairman. He has been the Chairman of the Board of Resource Capital Corp. since December 29, 2016. He serves as a Director of Emirates National Securitization Corporation. He has been a Director of M III Acquisition Corp. since July 2016. He has been a Director of Resource Capital Corp. since September 8, 2016. He is regularly appointed to and holds director positions in private, non-corporate vehicles controlled by Island Capital Group LLC. He served as a Director of Insignia Financial Group, Inc. since May 1998. He served as a Director of Istar Financial Inc. (now iStar Inc.) from May 2001 to 2003. He served as an Independent Trustee of Hunt Mortgage Group from 2004 to February 7, 2007. He served as a Trustee of Insignia Properties Trust since December 1996. He serves on the Board of the Peace Center for the Performing Arts, the YMCA, the Urban League and the Furman University Advisory Council. Mr. Farkas is a Member of the Young President' Organization and various other organizations. He is involved in The Fresh Air Fund, NARAL, the ASPCA, AMFAR and various other health, education and welfare oriented charities. Mr. Farkas received a B.A. in Econometrics from Harvard University in 1982.Read Full Background




